    dc:creator "Fourvel, Jean-Baptiste; Fosse, Philippe; Fernandez, Philippe; Antoine, Pierre-Olivier" ;
    dc:title "Coelodonta antiquitatis " ;
    trt:augmentsTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Coelodonta_antiquitatis_Blumenbach_1799> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.5252/g2015n2a5> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5252/g2015n2a5>
    bibo:endPage "266" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Geodiversitas" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2015-06-26" ;
    bibo:startPage "237" ;
    bibo:volume "37" ;
    dc:creator "Fourvel, Jean-Baptiste; Fosse, Philippe; Fernandez, Philippe; Antoine, Pierre-Olivier" ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Large mammals of Fouvent-Saint-Andoche (Haute-Saône, France): a glimpse into a Late Pleistocene hyena den" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4535143>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4535147>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4535149> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4535143>
    dc:description "FIG. 8. — Woolly rhinoceros Coelodonta antiquitatis (Blumenbach,1799) remains from Fouvent-Saint-Andoche (Coelodonta antiquitatis): A, D1; B-E, D2; F-H, D3; I-N, D4; O. d2; P, Q, d3; R-T, d4; U, V, M1; W, X, M2; Y, M3; Z, AA, humerus shaft cylinders; AB, AC, tibia shaft cylinders. Scale bar: 20 mm. Pictures by JBF." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4535143/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4535147>
    dc:description "FIG. 10. — Mortality curve of the woolly rhino (Coelodonta antiquitatis (Blumenbach, 1799)) from the late Pleistocene of Fouvent, based on dental eruption and wear stages. Modified from the protocol of Hillman-Smith et al. (1986), as detailed in Bacon et al. (2008)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4535147/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4535149>
    dc:description "FIG. 11. — Enamel hypoplasia on the tooth sample of Coelodonta antiquitatis (Blumenbach, 1799) (woolly rhino) from Fouvent: A, B, left d4 F11 C342, with a severe hypoplasia, characterized by the total lack of enamel on a part of the ectolophid (grey area). C, D, left M1 G9 D607; E, F, left M2 E11 B218. The last two teeth show less severe hypoplasia, visible through enamel constrictions on the lingual side (G9D607) and the ectoloph (F1 C243). These constrictions, parallel and remote, indicate the occurrence of two distinct episodes of physiological stress on each tooth. A, C, E, photographs. B, D, F, interpretative drawings (POA)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4535149/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

